node.text:
Spent 3 weeks  traveling, hosting retreats, nurturing and being nurtured by my beautiful @rekinectexperiences guests with my favorite Co-host 🌞. Gratitude to @lizzyjeff for seeing my joy, holding space and making sure EVERYONE around me knew I was an expecting mother 💙 and should be treated as such.  To my expecting mamas out there This is the most glorious time give yourself and baby all the pampering at all costs. If it costs your peace it’s too expensive. #blackjoy #expectingmama #blackmama 

Copper Crown 👑 to deflect negative energy, with water pearls for purity and citrine stones to attract prosperity and abundance made custom by @cianikal

node.text:
1 spot just opened for next week’s
retreat link in my bio for this very anticipated immersion into nature. 🙏🏾maybe it’s for you ❤️
.
So excited for our retreat under one week away ! I haven’t hosted a group of Queens in so long, and I am so empowered to do so with this life growing in my body.☀️giving me super powers
.
We got @lizzyjeff as our special guest keeping the feminine energy elevated with the affirmations and music. #divinefeminine 
.
@afreergem will be using her super-sensory intuitive gift to guide all of our guests more deeply into themselves.
.
This isn’t your typical Instagramable retreat this is an opportunity to truly heal with nature’s medicine and Kinect.
#rekinection #rekinectexperiences

- cacao ceremony 
- sacred waterfall bathing 

Hope to Rekinect with you soon 💓

node.text:
Thank you @guatemalavacationrentals @lakeatitlanlofts for this phenomenal stay. Thank you for taking care of my many cravings 😭 and creating a luxurious and relaxing experience.
.

 It’s a tradition of mine in to take a solo trip for my birthday for the last 5 years. I was a little torn on whether or not to travel this year because I just relocated to the Caribbean and I’m newly embarazada 🤰🏽. Living my best jungle life ya Girl desired LUXURY and time with self and ☀️ to connect. My sister and mamá of 2 @mitchygaines stressed the importance of staying who TF I am even in pregnancy because she said as a mama it can be easy to lose yourself ( start now she said)!

One way I love myself is giving myself the absolute best while traveling and making sensible splurges ! I also love Challenging myself to navigate fearless-ish through new territories. I now have  a wise person with unique needs inside of me that I have to listen to and bebe wanted to SLEEP not explore lol.

During my stay here i didn’t leave the house lol For  3 days I enjoyed a private cook, prenatal massages and hella SLEEP (in a Lizard free environment lol) it was divine. I hope some of this tender love for is absorbed by bebe ☀️ nothing but the best for mama and nothing but the best for ☀️
.
Hey mamas :
How did you love on yourself during 🤰🏽pregnancy?✍🏾

What’s something you wish you did while pregnant? ✍🏾

node.text:
#ad I’m partnering with @cerave to share their #heroesbehindthemasks campaign as part of their longstanding commitment to the nursing community and partnership with the American Nursing Association! The Heroes Behind the Masks campaign is designed to honor those who not only stand on the front lines of the global pandemic, but also work long hours every day to help others in their time of need. All you have to do is share your story at heroesbehindthemasks.com

 

I worked as a Critical Care Nurse for 8 years at some of the top institutions in the country. I worked in Cardiac Intensive Care, Liver Transplant Intensive Care, Trauma Intensive Care, and Neurosurgical Critical Care and as a travel RN for 5 years of my career. During my time at the bedside, I noticed all the selfless acts that I and my colleagues made on the daily basis. Nurses are truly special human beings, we work long hours without eating much, we only get a 30 min break in a 12-hour shift if we are lucky, we leave our families to take care of others, and we deal with people at the most vulnerable points in their lives. My career as a nurse taught me true empathy and compassion and I will forever pour into and love the medical community for all that they do! I have had the opportunity to share my nursing story in my various workshops, coaching programs, and retreats- now, it’s time to hear your story.

.
While the 250 CeraVe skincare kits have been claimed, there is still a chance to be one of the four winners selected to be featured in the Heroes Behind the Masks video series and to receive the Ultimate Spa Day treatment. The last day to enter the promotion is 11/6. These heroes will be featured as part of the video content series, in which they will share the stories that reveal their incredible commitment to the nursing profession and uplifting humanity!
.
Visit Heroesbehindthemasks.com to share your story #CeraVePartner

node.text:
30 Week Photo Dump

Traveled throughout Latin America for 6 months of my pregnancy. Planning, navigating, and SURRENDERING in new territory. Establishing new roots in a place where me and my baby can be as free as can be 💕. Girl I’m doing a good job 🌞

Gratitude to the WOMEN in my life who literally have held me up in this beautiful process. Thank you to the masculine who’ve stepped into support me and Sol . We lack nothing 🙏🏾

30 weeks ☺️💙 Today

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Monique Doughty BSN, RN on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.
Photo by Monique Doughty BSN, RN on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'We're really a generation of "This job not about to kill me"'.

node.text:
As I kick my feet up in the jungle approaching my 7 month of pregnancy I know the ancestors are proud.  After having two successful healing retreats for women I decided it’s time to put myself on maternity leave 🙏🏾 bless it. 
You see my mom worked her entire pregnancy and went into labor while WORKING issa hell nah for me lol. 

I’m a single expecting mother, self employed and living abroad… fear kicks in hella often.  Low frequency thoughts come into the field like “worst case scenario I’ll get a job doing … “ higher frequency thoughts remind me to TRUST the stability of myself and that I can CHOOSE to do what I enjoy for currency. 

When I came to the conclusion that I was on this journey to parenthood without any financial support other than my black owned business and my personal assets I got a little shook. But this thing I teach called SELF LOVE won’t allow me to push myself in any directions that aren’t fully me… and that means a job IDFW will not get my energy. I teach a course called 6 weeks to Self Love it was so highly anticipated that I made it self guided and pre recorded, understand that Self Love will put you into situations that are of your highest good and take you out of situations that don’t deserve you. It’s the first step doing what you love. Stop letting that job be bout to kill and get you some self love/ self worth.
Self Guided 6 Weeks To Self Love Program at the link in my bio ❤️🙏🏾
👇🏾👇🏾👇🏾
How are you showing yourself love in your career ? 👇🏾
How are you honoring your truth in your work? 👇🏾

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Monique Doughty BSN, RN on July 29, 2021 tagging @ebi_eats. May be an image of 1 person, beard and indoor.

node.text:
I’ve been silent because my mind has been very loud 🙏🏾 processing the lost of @ebi_eats creator of #nurselifeRN.  So often we jump to honor people publicly but forget  to honor them in private. Ive been looking through the memories of traveling and working with Ebi and I have to say this loss is a painful one. I’ve been Praying over his Family.
.
Ebi and I were pioneers of nurses in Media, particularly black nurses in media. I met Ebi in 2017 when I was in the midst of building my cute little nurse empire. He was stoked to sit with me to make a whole plan for his business and he said “ I just wanna make funny memes and bring some humor to this profession “… that’s what he did and some.  He surpassed what I taught him, grew his audience beyond a million in a matter of 2 years of meeting him but he always made me feel like a star and bigged me up for my growth. 
.
I spoke on many panels with Ebi, we we were the only brown faces on many sets shooting scrubs and medical apparel, we had many late night plotting/ planning calls with him on how to elevate beyond being a pawn in healthcare or with these brands that used our likeness for their personal gain. We would talk shi* about those companies that tried to exploit us ( y’all know who y’all are ) but we always kept it classy, never blasted anyone just focusing on our brand’s elevating. 

Ebi was awake, not green at all, his sense of humor was playful but this man built a community that supported many of us, he created some of the coolest products, a shoeline for nurses and safe spaces for us to vent and most importantly LAUGH. 
.
Ebi and I shared the common goal of wanting to be free, not work for anyone and to tend to our plants lol. Now Ebi can be as free as can be.
.
To everyone who kinda knew Ebi thank you for sharing your memories . For everyone who really knew Ebi you know he would want y’all to laugh and not give an energy to any BS. A few lessons from Ebi
1. Don’t take anyone or anything too serious 
2. Follow your dream even if it’s as simple as I’m gonna make people laugh ( do that )
3. Water your plants 

May he Rest In Peace 🙏🏾

node.text:
Spent 3 weeks  traveling, hosting retreats, nurturing and being nurtured by my beautiful @rekinectexperiences guests with my favorite Co-host 🌞. Gratitude to @lizzyjeff for seeing my joy, holding space and making sure EVERYONE around me knew I was an expecting mother 💙 and should be treated as such.  To my expecting mamas out there This is the most glorious time give yourself and baby all the pampering at all costs. If it costs your peace it’s too expensive. #blackjoy #expectingmama #blackmama 

Copper Crown 👑 to deflect negative energy, with water pearls for purity and citrine stones to attract prosperity and abundance made custom by @cianikal

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Monique Doughty BSN, RN on July 11, 2021 tagging @hestiaselfloveexperience. May be an image of 1 person and body of water.

node.text:
Me and 🌞’s co•creator wanted a little girl, we saw her clearly and she spoke to both of us deeply. We knew she was coming, I saw her in waterfalls and she would laugh and sing with me when I was riding my bike in the SUNSHINE through the tropics rubbing my little tummy. He would buy her gifts mad early and sing to my itty bitty belly. We told stories about her future adventures, planned to build a home, created music, art and loved ourselves in our own ways . Mine was loving myself enough to give myself and baby all of me. 
As the presence of her co creator shifted to absent, it rained a lot. Me and 🌞 moved into a little apartment on the beach and I had a phase where I detached from our connection, Mother wasn’t available to Sunshine because there was so much rain and pain. Sunshine reminded me to eat, put my toes in the sand, get sunshine and stay open to Support and welcome community. We had each other. Baby held me. Sunshine turned into a Strong Soul that guided me, he manifested houses, financial  blessings,  a fire 🔥 tribe, moved life around and didn’t accept no as an answer. Sunshine became Sol’Sharif a noble king who protects me and guides me to all the right decisions. Sunshine chose us, Sol’ Sharif is choosing me. Welcome baby Boy 💙 

We receive what we need, thank you baby for guiding us to being as Free as we can be.

node.text:
My choice to move abroad was necessary in my conscious  choice to become a mother. Fear will test us but we have to bet on ourselves 🙏🏾 Stability is a mindset that I teach in my Self Love Course, now available self paced at the link in my bio. 
.
Recently I sat down with the Goddesses @goodmoms_badchoices and shared my imperfect story of becoming a mama and being FREE as can be. Check out “ Black Pregnant and Abroad” at the link in my bio available on all streaming platforms.
.
How are you defining your stability 👇🏾👇🏾👇🏾

.
So excited for our retreat under one week away ! I haven’t hosted a group of Queens in so long, and I am so empowered to do so with this life growing in my body.☀️giving me super powers
.
We got @lizzyjeff as our special guest keeping the feminine energy elevated with the affirmations and music. #divinefeminine 
.
@afreergem will be using her super-sensory intuitive gift to guide all of our guests more deeply into themselves.
.
This isn’t your typical Instagramable retreat this is an opportunity to truly heal with nature’s medicine and Kinect.
#rekinection #rekinectexperiences

node.text:
I’m learning from Baby Sunshine 🌞 

A few lessons he/she has taught me in in our 19 weeks together.
From the desk of 🌞
1. Surrender I’m writing the story not you
2.  Comfort at all costs Don’t get cheap we ain’t cut out to rough it no more
3. Let go of all dietary programing feed me what i ask for mama 
4. Rest that’s when I grow 
5. If it hurts mama’s heart it stunts my growth, let it go
6. It’s me and you and everyone else is appreciated but it’s US
7.  Call Grandma @queen_elaceybacon a lot lol 
8. Ask for help and accept it
9. Enjoy every moment with me 
10. Sit back and I’ll bring everything our way we need ( master manifester 🌞) 
.
We gotta listen to these growing beings they have messages from the spirit realm, untouched by fear or programing 🙏🏾 for my mamas 
What number can you relate to most 👇🏾
What did your growing baby teach you ?👇🏾
.
Side note I find out the sex of baby this week and I’m so hype, their gender changes with my mood ❤️🤰🏽 and energy I’m feeling for the day lol. I was so sure now i need receipts !

node.text:
*** 1/3 of The Aunties****
I sent out a VERY detailed PDF lol with travel instructions and none of them read it 😭 but, they showed up/out and they showered us in love, smuggles and MAD Amazon packages and @traderjoes snack ( bless them i can’t get them here)🙏🏾 Gratitude to y’all for taking multiple flights, a 5 hour car ride, dealing with mosquitoes, monkeys, humidity, a bat 🦇 that got into my house 😭 ( normal ) and lizards all to love on me and Sunshine 🌞. My bad for not really warning y’all of all that comes with the tropics but y’all handled jungle life gracefully. Everybody loves  Sunshine, I’m grateful baby 🌞is so wanted.

node.text:
5 months in Costa Rica and this is the type of support that my baby has called in. I give 🌞 Sunshine all the glory for removing anyone and anything that didn’t serve our greatest and highest and calling in Community, unconditional love, discernment, guidance from our ancestors and big support. I can’t take credit for all the miracles in my life, Children have the power to manifest and call in whatever is needed so never view them as a burden  or bill they are blessings ! 
They say it takes a village and baby 🌞 we’ve got one from all over the 🌍 world. Our home is in the tropics until we decide to roam again ❤️. 
.
Over the last year I’ve been working on my ability to accept support. Learning to say YES when someone offers ..to access my throat chakra and say, “ yoooo can you help me “🙏🏾 without feeling shame. Little did I know when we open ourselves up to support, support shows up in abundance.. not always the way we pictured it. I accept all blessings in the forms they come in.
.
When I moved to Costa Rica I stayed because this is where I wanted to raise black children. This land made me feel welcomed to extend my bloodline and to do so safely, naturally and above all FREELY!

I fell deeply in love with the medicine, ocean, land, the people, the food and the Caribbean flavor. Thank you all for holding me and ☀️ close, praying with and for us, teaching us,
Protecting us and loving us. Bless this community. 
.
To my online community who send me and ☀️ prayers, well wishes and High vibrations THANK YOU, we value you, please keep them coming, I feel all 129K of y’all rooting for especially in our times of pain. It’s not always perfect and I appreciate y’all 
.
Pictures shot at my Kundalini Celebration, it’s a yogic tradition,  120 days from the baby’s conception date, where the baby receives a soul seperate from their mother’s. On this day I became a mother. My friends and family gathered to support me on my journey to becoming a mother. 
.
#motherhood  #maidentomamma #tropics #journeytomotherhood
